                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290115-223-off1196 t18290115-223-victim1754"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182901150099"></xptr>
            
                  <persName id="t18290115-223-person1755">
                  JAMES 
                  BONNER
               <interp inst="t18290115-223-person1755" type="surname" value="BONNER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-223-person1755" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-223-person1755" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18290115-223-viclabel1198" type="occupation">labourer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290115-223-victim1754 t18290115-223-viclabel1198"></join>. I had this money in a bag, in my right-hand waistcoat pocket on the 6th of December; the prisoner and I went into a public-house, and had a drop of beer - I happened to fall asleep; I do not know that I had been drinking too much - I went in there between one and two o'clock, and awoke between five and six; the prisoner and my money were then gone - I knew him before; he is a <rs id="t18290115-223-deflabel1199" type="occupation">labourer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290115-223-defend1753 t18290115-223-deflabel1199"></join> - I went to look after him, but could not find him, till the next night, which was Sunday; I cannot think of the name of the place - Mr. Cooper took him, and found some money on him; I charged him with taking it, and he delivered up the money he had left, and did not say he had not taken it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q.Did not you sleep with me on Saturday night? A. Yes, and asked him for my money; he used very bad language.</p>
               <p>WILLIAM BOARD. I am a labourer. I was having a pint of beer, between nine and ten o'clock; the prisoner came, and asked me if I would take 1l. 11s. to his daughter - I received from him a sovereign, a half-sovereign, and 1s.; he said he was going on a tramp - he has a son, who has lost the use of his limbs, and I was to give this to his daughter, while she was in trouble; on the Monday she came and had the sovereign, and said her father was in trouble.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290115-223-person1756">
                  JOSEPH 
                  COOPER
               <interp inst="t18290115-223-person1756" type="surname" value="COOPER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-223-person1756" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-223-person1756" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I found the prisoner in a room in Johnson's-place, sitting on the floor, in a state of intoxication - I asked what he had done with Bonner's money; he said, "I have got it;" I said,"Produce it" - he pulled out three sovereigns, a half-sovereign, and 7s. in other money; the next morning, his daughter came - I got this sovereign from her.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. When he came to my house, he asked for me; he slept with me that night - we went and had something to drink, and he never came near me till the Sunday afternoon; I ran from place to place to find him; he gave me this money, with his own hand, as he was intoxicated.</p>
               <p>JURY to JAMES BONNER. Q.Did you give him the money? A. I cannot say.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18290115-223-verdict1200" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18290115-223-verdict1200" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               NOT GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
